All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
GraphDriver
The GraphDriver class that tests basic functionality of the Graph class.
GraphInterface<T>
An interface to implement methods related to Graphs.
ListGraph<T>
An implementation of the GraphInterface interface to store graphs using an Adjacency List We have variables for the list itself, a list of vertices, and a number of edges calculation.
ListGraphTest
This is the testing class we use to test the methods we implemented for List Graph.
ListInterface<T>
The ListInterface interface which we later implement to create a ResizeableList.
MatrixGraph<T>
An implementation of the GraphInterface interface to store graphs using an Adjacency Matrix We have variables for the matrix itself, a list of vertices, and a number of edges calculation.
MatrixGraphTest
This is the testing class we use to test the methods we implemented for Matrix Graph.
Queue<T>
The Queue class that implements the QueueInterface interface.
QueueDriver
The QueueDriver class that tests basic functionality of the Queue class.
QueueInterface<T>
An interface to implement methods related to Queues.
ResizeableList<T>
The ResizeableList class that implements the ListInterface interface.
ResizeableListDriver
The ResizeableListDriver class that tests basic functionality of the ResizeableList class.
Stack<T>
An implementation of the StackInterface interface to create Stacks using a resizeable list We have variable for the list itself which is created using a LIFO (Last In First Out) approach The three methods for a stack are Push, Peek, and Pop, but there are also various methods like clear and isEmpty.
StackDriver
The StackDriver class that tests basic functionality of the Stack class.
StackInterface<T>
An interface to implement methods related to Stacks.
